definitions.definition: To move more quickly than (someone or something) so as to outrun or leave it behind .
examples: We quickly outstripped the amateur runners.

definitions.definition: To exceed or surpass (someone or something).
examples: This year’s production has already outstripped last year’s.

definitions.definition: To exceed or overstep (a boundary or limit ); to transgress .

main_definition: To move more quickly than (someone or something) so as to outrun or leave it behind .
secondary_definitions: ( figuratively ) To exceed or surpass (someone or something).
( archaic , rare ) To exceed or overstep (a boundary or limit ); to transgress .
